*

00:39.640 --> 00:41.142
- HERE'S WHERE RAGE
AND ZEPHYR

00:41.175 --> 00:42.676
DISCOVER J.T. BEATEN
AND LEFT FOR DEAD

00:42.710 --> 00:44.678
BY A GANG
OF GAY BASHERS.

00:44.712 --> 00:46.114
- IT'S KIND OF GORY.

00:46.147 --> 00:47.215
- IT'S SUPPOSED TO BE.

00:47.248 --> 00:48.582
- I'M SURE
THAT I LEFT IT HERE.

00:48.616 --> 00:49.550
- HERE'S RAGE

00:49.583 --> 00:52.320
ZAPPING THE BASHERS
WITH HIS MIND DISTORTER.

00:52.353 --> 00:53.621
- WITH HIS WHAT?

00:53.654 --> 00:55.689
- HE SURROUNDS THEM
WITH A MIND DISTORTION FIELD

00:55.723 --> 00:57.325
SO THEY THINK
THEY'RE ALL FAGS.

00:57.358 --> 00:59.193
- THEN THEY
BEAT EACH OTHER TO DEATH.

00:59.227 --> 01:01.562
- WOW.
THEN WHAT HAPPENS?

01:01.595 --> 01:04.098
- THEN HE SWOOPS J.T.
INTO HIS ARMS

01:04.132 --> 01:05.799
AND TAKES HIM
UP TO HIS LAIR

01:05.833 --> 01:07.568
PERCHED HIGH ABOVE
GAYOPOLIS...

01:07.601 --> 01:09.403
- AND HE BRINGS J.T.
BACK TO LIFE

01:09.437 --> 01:11.639
WITH LOTS OF HEAVY KISSING
AND DEEP ANAL PENETRATION.

01:11.672 --> 01:13.141
- WHICH, IF YOU'LL NOTICE

01:13.174 --> 01:15.409
FROM THE GENEROUS AMOUNTS
OF ILLUSTRATIONS,

01:15.443 --> 01:16.844
IS JUSTIN'S
FAVORITE PART.

01:16.877 --> 01:18.212
- YES, I SEE.

01:18.246 --> 01:20.514
OKAY, WHERE THE HELL
IS MY PALM?

01:20.548 --> 01:22.250
- MM, WELL, TRY MY BEDROOM.

01:22.283 --> 01:23.851
YOU KNOW, IT MAY HAVE
DROPPED OUT OF YOUR POCKET

01:23.884 --> 01:25.319
WHILE YOU WERE DROPPING OUT
OF YOUR PANTS.

01:25.353 --> 01:28.489
- MM, GOOD THINKING,
BOY-TOY WONDER.

01:35.496 --> 01:36.464
- YOU STOLE IT?

01:36.497 --> 01:37.631
- [whispering]
BORROWED IT.

01:37.665 --> 01:38.899
BEN'S GOT A BUDDY LIST
IN HERE.

01:38.932 --> 01:40.334
SO I'M GONNA
CALL EVERYBODY ON IT

01:40.368 --> 01:41.869
AND INVITE THEM
TO A SURPRISE PARTY.

01:41.902 --> 01:43.671
- WHEN'S HIS BIRTHDAY?
- SATURDAY.

01:43.704 --> 01:44.805
- NO SHIT, THAT'S MINE.

01:44.838 --> 01:47.741
- REALLY?
- YEAH.

01:47.775 --> 01:50.211
ISN'T THAT THE MOST AMAZING
COINCIDENCE?

01:50.244 --> 01:51.912
- WHAT, THAT YOU TWO
HAVE THE SAME BIRTHDAY?

01:51.945 --> 01:53.647
- OR THAT YOU AND BRIAN
ARE BOTH IN LOVE

01:53.681 --> 01:56.150
WITH GUYS
WHO HAVE THE SAME BIRTHDAY.

01:56.184 --> 01:58.452
- AHH, NO LUCK
IN THE BEDROOM.

01:58.486 --> 02:00.454
- THAT'S A FIRST.

02:00.488 --> 02:01.889
[buzzer]

02:01.922 --> 02:04.325
- YOU KNOW, I KNOW THAT MY
PALM'S STATE-OF-THE-ART, BUT...

02:04.358 --> 02:06.227
COULDN'T HAVE JUST WALKED AWAY
ON ITS OWN.

02:06.260 --> 02:07.228
- YOU WANT TO STAY FOR
DINNER?

02:07.261 --> 02:08.629
BEN'S MAKING PAD THAI.

02:08.662 --> 02:09.863
- THEN...

02:09.897 --> 02:11.865
WE ARE GOING TO WATCH...

02:11.899 --> 02:13.501
SUNSET BOULEVARD.

02:13.534 --> 02:15.369
- I CAN'T.

02:15.403 --> 02:16.770
BRIAN AND I ARE GOING TO...

02:16.804 --> 02:17.771
BABYLON.
- BABYLON.

02:17.805 --> 02:19.740
- BABYLON, YEAH.

02:19.773 --> 02:22.743
[upbeat music]

02:22.776 --> 02:24.512
*

02:24.545 --> 02:27.515
- WHOO! YEAH!

02:27.548 --> 02:33.221
*

02:33.254 --> 02:36.490
- ISN'T THAT, LIKE,
THE MOST AMAZING COINCIDENCE?

02:36.524 --> 02:38.659
- THAT YOU BEN AND, LIKE,
17 MILLION OTHER PEOPLE

02:38.692 --> 02:41.262
HAVE THE SAME BIRTHDAY?

02:41.295 --> 02:42.930
- SO HOW DO YOU PLAN ON
COMMEMORATING THE BIG EVENT?

02:42.963 --> 02:45.266
A TRIP TO KEY WEST?

02:45.299 --> 02:47.601
SOMETHING WITH FOUR WHEELS
AND A RETRACTABLE HARD-TOP?

02:47.635 --> 02:48.702
- THAT SOUNDS GOOD.

02:48.736 --> 02:49.870
- I'M NOT.

02:49.903 --> 02:51.672
- YOU'RE NOT?

02:51.705 --> 02:53.541
- WHAT'S A FUCKING BIRTHDAY?

02:53.574 --> 02:55.976
ANYBODY CAN GET BORN,
EVEN YOU.

02:56.009 --> 02:59.547
THE ONLY THING WORTH
CELEBRATING IS ACHIEVEMENT.

02:59.580 --> 03:00.914
- I SEEM TO REMEMBER YOU

03:00.948 --> 03:03.851
THROWING MICHAEL A LITTLE
SURPRISE PARTY LAST YEAR.

03:03.884 --> 03:05.353
- I AGREE WITH BRIAN.

03:05.386 --> 03:07.321
I THINK BIRTHDAYS
ARE SILLY,

03:07.355 --> 03:09.890
SENTIMENTAL,
AND UNNECESSARY.

03:09.923 --> 03:10.991
- OKAY, SWEETHEART,

03:11.024 --> 03:12.626
THANKS FOR THE RIDE,
BUT, UH,

03:12.660 --> 03:15.429
HERE'S WHERE I GET OFF.

03:16.797 --> 03:19.400
- SOME CATCH. HOW COME
YOU'RE THROWING HIM BACK?

03:19.433 --> 03:20.668
- NOT BIG ENOUGH?

03:20.701 --> 03:22.903
- OH, I'M SURE
HE'S BIG ENOUGH.

03:22.936 --> 03:24.372
- YOU STILL IN MOURNING?

03:24.405 --> 03:26.006
- I'VE TRIED BOYS,
I'VE TRIED BOOZE,

03:26.039 --> 03:27.641
I'VE TRIED PILLS...

03:27.675 --> 03:31.879
BUT I AM STILL IN THE VALLEY
OF THE DULLS.

03:31.912 --> 03:35.849
- WELL, NEELY, MAYBE YOU NEED
SOME SPIRITUAL SUCCOR.

03:35.883 --> 03:37.551
- YEAH, YOU SHOULD CALL
MY MOTHER'S MINISTER.

03:37.585 --> 03:39.487
HE GIVES GREAT HEAD.

03:39.520 --> 03:41.689
- THAT'S NOT THE KIND OF
HEALING I HAD IN MIND.

03:41.722 --> 03:45.459
YOU'RE COMING WITH ME
TOMORROW...

03:45.493 --> 03:47.495
TO CHURCH.

03:47.528 --> 03:48.962
- CHURCH?

03:48.996 --> 03:50.464
- THE CURTAIN
HAS ALREADY GONE UP

03:50.498 --> 03:52.466
ON THE BIGGEST SHOW
IN TOWN,

03:52.500 --> 03:54.968
IN THE UNIVERSE,
IN CREATION.

03:55.002 --> 03:57.871
IT'S CALLED "YOUR LIFE"!

03:57.905 --> 03:59.340
AND IT STARS YOU.

03:59.373 --> 04:01.375
THE ORIGINAL CAST,
WITH LYRICS AND MUSIC,

04:01.409 --> 04:03.877
AND A BOOK THAT COULD ONLY
HAVE BEEN WRITTEN,

04:03.911 --> 04:08.316
DIRECTED,
AND CONCEIVED BY...

04:08.349 --> 04:09.350
GOD!

04:09.383 --> 04:10.618
all: AMEN.

04:10.651 --> 04:13.321
- ISN'T REVEREND BRAD
INCREDIBLE?

04:13.354 --> 04:16.457
- YEAH, YEAH, HE SHOULD...
WIN A TONY.

04:16.490 --> 04:18.626
- THIS IS NOT
A DRESS REHEARSAL, KIDS.

04:18.659 --> 04:20.961
LET US SELL IT
TO THE BALCONY AND BEYOND.

04:20.994 --> 04:22.830
RISE, RISE,

04:22.863 --> 04:24.064
AND FOLLOW IN YOUR HYMNALS.

04:24.097 --> 04:27.601
[organ playing]

04:27.635 --> 04:28.869
HIT IT.

04:28.902 --> 04:30.338
* PUT ON
YOUR SUNDAY CLOTHES *

04:30.371 --> 04:33.874
* WHEN YOU FEEL
DOWN AND OUT *

04:33.907 --> 04:36.344
* STRUT DOWN THE STREET
AND HAVE YOUR PICTURE TOOK *

04:36.377 --> 04:38.078
- IMAGINE
HOW GOOD YOU'LL FEEL.

04:38.111 --> 04:39.747
- I THINK IT'S GOING TO TAKE
A LITTLE MORE THAN A SHOW TUNE.

04:39.780 --> 04:43.617
- * LIKE A DREAM, YOUR SPIRIT
SEEMS TO TURN ABOUT *

04:43.651 --> 04:46.420
- HERE, SHARE MINE.
- THANKS.

04:46.454 --> 04:49.590
- * A CERTAIN SIGN THAT
YOU FEEL AS FINE AS YOU LOOK *

04:49.623 --> 04:54.662
* WHEN YOU WEAR A SONG
THE WORLD IS ALL A SMILE *

04:54.695 --> 04:57.398
* THAT MAKES YOU FEEL BRAND-NEW
DOWN TO YOUR TOES *

04:57.431 --> 04:58.999
OH!

04:59.032 --> 05:01.034
* GET OUT YOUR FEATHERS,
YOUR... *

05:01.068 --> 05:02.670
- YOU KNOW, I ACTUALLY
DO FEEL BETTER.

05:02.703 --> 05:04.071
- * YOUR BUTTONS AND BOWS

05:04.104 --> 05:05.673
* FOR THERE'S
NO BLUE MONDAY *

05:05.706 --> 05:09.009
* IN YOUR SUNDAY CLOTHES

05:09.042 --> 05:11.812
- COME ON, BARNABY,
LET'S GO TO PITTSBURGH.

05:11.845 --> 05:14.415
- I WAS WITH THE PEACE CORPS
FOR A FEW YEARS,

05:14.448 --> 05:16.049
BUT THEN, I DECIDED
WHAT I REALLY WANTED

05:16.083 --> 05:18.952
WAS TO WORK WITH KIDS.
- THAT'S SWEET.

05:18.986 --> 05:21.054
- HUH.
EVER TEACH SECOND-GRADERS?

05:21.088 --> 05:23.691
SWEET'S NOT EXACTLY THE WORD.
- [chuckling]

05:23.724 --> 05:25.859
I'M SURE THEY ADORE YOU.

05:25.893 --> 05:27.127
- I LOVE IT.

05:27.160 --> 05:28.796
AND IT ALLOWS ME TIME
IN THE EVENINGS

05:28.829 --> 05:30.698
TO VOLUNTEER AT THE GAY YOUTH
SUPPORT LINE

05:30.731 --> 05:33.100
AND TO TRAIN FOR THE AIDS RIDE
ON THE WEEKEND.

05:33.133 --> 05:36.470
AND THEN, OF COURSE, I, UH...
HELP OUT AT THE CHURCH.

05:36.504 --> 05:38.672
- OF COURSE. HEH.

05:38.706 --> 05:39.907
I'M IMPRESSED.

05:39.940 --> 05:42.943
- LISTEN TO ME GOING ON
ABOUT MYSELF.

05:42.976 --> 05:45.679
WHAT ABOUT YOU?

05:45.713 --> 05:47.415
TELL ME WHAT YOU DO.

05:47.448 --> 05:49.116
- ME?
- MM-HMM.

05:49.149 --> 05:52.119
[techno music]

05:52.152 --> 05:55.022
*

05:55.055 --> 05:57.090
TED?

05:57.124 --> 05:58.626
- HMM?

05:58.659 --> 05:59.960
WHERE'D YOU JUST GO?

05:59.993 --> 06:02.095
- OH, UH...

06:02.129 --> 06:03.764
NOWHERE.
I WAS, UH...

06:03.797 --> 06:06.567
JUST THINKING
ABOUT WHAT YOU SAID.

06:06.600 --> 06:09.503
- SO, UH, WHAT DO YOU DO?

06:09.537 --> 06:12.506
- I, UH...
WORK IN COMPUTERS.

06:12.540 --> 06:14.875
- UM, SALES?
PROGRAMMING?

06:14.908 --> 06:18.479
- I RUN MY OWN DOT-COM
COMPANY.

06:18.512 --> 06:20.113
- REALLY?

06:20.147 --> 06:21.849
AN ENTREPRENEUR.

06:21.882 --> 06:24.585
SO, UH, WHAT KIND OF
COMPANY IS IT?

06:24.618 --> 06:26.787
- YOU KNOW...

06:26.820 --> 06:28.889
DEALING WITH PEOPLE'S NEEDS.

06:31.625 --> 06:33.427
YOU MIGHT CALL IT...

06:33.461 --> 06:35.028
RELIEF WORK.

06:35.062 --> 06:36.530
- SOMEHOW I...

06:36.564 --> 06:37.665
I KNEW YOU'D DO SOMETHING

06:37.698 --> 06:41.502
THAT INVOLVED
HELPING OTHERS.

06:41.535 --> 06:44.037
- A SURPRISE PARTY?

06:44.071 --> 06:45.172
SO WHAT DO YOU PLAN TO DO?

06:45.205 --> 06:47.040
- DO?
- YEAH, YOU KNOW,

06:47.074 --> 06:48.108
AFTER EVERYONE
JUMPS OUT OF THE WOODWORK

06:48.141 --> 06:49.309
AND SCREAMS "SURPRISE"?

06:49.342 --> 06:51.779
- I DON'T KNOW. I-I THOUGHT
WE'D SING HAPPY BIRTHDAY

06:51.812 --> 06:53.881
AND CUT THE CAKE,
OPEN PRESENTS.

06:53.914 --> 06:55.583
- ANY THOUGHT OF NUDITY
AND DRUGS?

06:55.616 --> 06:57.785
- THIS ISN'T
ONE OF YOUR AFFAIRS.

06:57.818 --> 06:59.653
BESIDES,
I'M NOT ROLLING IN DOUGH.

06:59.687 --> 07:01.522
I CAN'T AFFORD
SOME ELABORATE PARTY.

07:01.555 --> 07:03.023
- SWEETHEART, YOU DON'T NEED
A LOT OF MONEY,

07:03.056 --> 07:04.925
YOU JUST NEED A THEME.

07:04.958 --> 07:06.059
WHAT'S, UH,
WHAT'S BEN INTO?

07:06.093 --> 07:07.995
- YOGA, BUDDHISM.

07:08.028 --> 07:10.163
- OH, WE CAN MEDITATE!

07:10.197 --> 07:11.632
THAT SOUNDS LIKE FUN.

07:11.665 --> 07:12.766
- OKAY, GIVE ME A MINUTE HERE.

07:12.800 --> 07:15.002
LET ME THINK,
LET ME THINK.

07:15.035 --> 07:18.672
OKAY, OKAY, IT'S COMING TO ME.
I'M GETTING AN IDEA.

07:18.706 --> 07:19.940
WHY DON'T WE DO

07:19.973 --> 07:22.676
A GEISHA-SUSHI-"MISS-SAIGONY"
KIND OF THING?

07:22.710 --> 07:24.111
WE CAN TRANSFORM
BEN'S APARTMENT

07:24.144 --> 07:26.980
INTO A FAR EASTERN
PHANTASMAGORIA

07:27.014 --> 07:28.215
WITH COLORED LANTERNS

07:28.248 --> 07:31.218
AND, UM, LITTLE...
PAGODAS.

07:31.251 --> 07:33.120
- YEAH.
BETTER YET,

07:33.153 --> 07:34.688
WHY DON'T YOU BUY
A BOTTLE OF SAKE

07:34.722 --> 07:36.256
AND A COPY OF THE KAMA SUTRA

07:36.289 --> 07:38.826
AND FUCK YOUR BRAINS OUT?

07:38.859 --> 07:40.027
IT'LL BE CHEAPER.

07:40.060 --> 07:41.729
- HONEY, YOU JUST
LEAVE IT TO ME.

07:41.762 --> 07:44.565
I WILL MAKE SURE IT IS A PARTY
THAT'S UNFORGETTABLE.

07:44.598 --> 07:46.199
- WHO'S HAVING A PARTY?

07:46.233 --> 07:48.235
- NOBODY.

07:48.268 --> 07:51.505
- MUSTN'T BE MUCH
OF A GUEST LIST.

07:51.539 --> 07:53.106
- BEN'S BIRTHDAY.

07:53.140 --> 07:55.142
AND MICHAEL'S GOING TO
THROW HIM A FAR EASTERN...

07:55.175 --> 07:59.580
PHANTASMAGORIA .

07:59.613 --> 08:01.048
- THAT'S NICE.

08:03.050 --> 08:04.151
[bell dings]

08:04.184 --> 08:06.153
- HEY, DEB,
YOUR ORDER'S UP.

08:06.186 --> 08:07.955
- ORDER'S UP.

08:07.988 --> 08:09.056
GOTTA GET BACK TO WORK.

08:11.592 --> 08:12.860
- WHAT THE FUCK
YOU TELL HER FOR?

08:12.893 --> 08:14.895
- WHY THE FUCK DO YOU WANT
TO KEEP IT A SECRET?

08:14.928 --> 08:17.097
- BECAUSE I DON'T WANT HER TO
GIVE ME ANY MORE SHIT ABOUT BEN.

08:17.130 --> 08:19.700
- MAYBE IF YOU INVITED HER...

08:19.733 --> 08:22.770
- WHAT FOR?
SHE WOULDN'T COME ANYWAY.

08:22.803 --> 08:24.805
- WHAT DO YOU MEAN,
HE'S NOT DOING ANYTHING?

08:24.838 --> 08:26.907
- BRIAN DOESN'T BELIEVE IN
BIRTHDAYS, NOT EVEN HIS OWN.

08:26.940 --> 08:28.776
- WHAT KIND OF
BULLSHIT IS THAT?

08:28.809 --> 08:30.644
- HE ALMOST KILLED HIMSELF
WHEN HE TURNED 30.

08:30.678 --> 08:31.979
- YEAH, WHO'S TALKING
ABOUT HIS BIRTHDAY?

08:32.012 --> 08:33.146
WE'RE TALKING
ABOUT JUSTIN'S.

08:33.180 --> 08:34.915
WHAT'S HIS PROBLEM
WITH TURNING 19?

08:34.948 --> 08:36.850
- HE BELIEVES IN CELEBRATING
ACCOMPLISHMENT,

08:36.884 --> 08:37.885
NOT SENTIMENTAL RITUALS.

08:37.918 --> 08:39.019
- OH, BLAH, BLAH, BLAH.

08:39.052 --> 08:40.988
WHAT THE HELL DID HE DO,
BRAINWASH YOU?

08:41.021 --> 08:44.024
EVERYBODY DESERVES A LITTLE
ATTENTION ON THEIR BIRTHDAY.

08:44.057 --> 08:46.193
- ESPECIALLY FROM THE PERSON
THEY LOVE.

08:46.226 --> 08:47.695
[giggling]

08:47.728 --> 08:50.030
WELL, IF BRIAN'S NOT GOING
TO DO ANYTHING, WE WILL.

08:50.063 --> 08:52.966
- YEAH. WHAT DO YOU SAY WE, UH,
GO TO DINNER AND A MOVIE?

08:53.000 --> 08:55.202
- OH, THAT'S NOT VERY SPECIAL.
WE CAN DO THAT ANYTIME.

08:55.235 --> 08:57.137
- OKAY,
LET'S THROW A PARTY.

08:57.170 --> 08:59.840
- I HATE PARTIES.
- HE HATES PARTIES.

08:59.873 --> 09:01.709
- BESIDES, MICHAEL'S
ALREADY GIVING BEN ONE.

09:01.742 --> 09:04.645
- I KNOW. YOU'RE COMING WITH US,
SATURDAY AFTERNOON.

09:04.678 --> 09:06.046
- WHERE?

09:06.079 --> 09:07.615
- A FRIEND OF MINE WHO TEACHES
IN THE MUSIC DEPARTMENT

09:07.648 --> 09:11.084
AT YOUR SCHOOL INVITED US
TO A VIOLIN RECITAL.

09:11.118 --> 09:12.686
- A VIOLIN RECITAL?

09:12.720 --> 09:14.955
- SHE SAID THE STUDENT
WHO'S PLAYING IS A GENIUS.

09:14.988 --> 09:16.790
- I'M NOT REALLY
INTO CLASSICAL MUSIC.

09:16.824 --> 09:18.291
- WELL, MAYBE IT'S TIME
YOU EXPOSED YOURSELF

09:18.325 --> 09:20.227
TO A HIGHER FORM
OF CULTURAL EXPRESSION

09:20.260 --> 09:22.663
THAN THE THUMPA-THUMPA
AT BABYLON.

09:22.696 --> 09:24.698
- WELL, IF HE DOESN'T WANT
TO GO, DON'T FORCE HIM.

09:24.732 --> 09:27.334
ALTHOUGH SHE ALSO SAID
HE'S REALLY CUTE.

09:27.367 --> 09:31.271
[giggling]

09:31.304 --> 09:32.873
- [mouth full]
WHY DIDN'T YOU SAY SO?

09:32.906 --> 09:36.243
[indistinct chatter]

09:36.276 --> 09:39.079
- AHH.
THESE ARE FOR YOU.

09:39.112 --> 09:40.714
- BUT IT'S YOUR BIRTHDAY.

09:40.748 --> 09:43.316
- WELL, YOU KNOW WHAT THEY SAY,
IT'S BETTER TO GIVE.

09:43.350 --> 09:45.619
- WELL, RECEIVING'S
NOT TOO BAD EITHER.

09:45.653 --> 09:46.787
- MMM.
- YOU KNOW, WHILE WE'RE

09:46.820 --> 09:48.155
ON THE SUBJECT
OF YOUR BIRTHDAY...

09:48.188 --> 09:49.957
- YES, WHILE WE'RE ON IT,
PLEASE, NOTHING SPECIAL.

09:49.990 --> 09:53.293
LET'S JUST KEEP IT SIMPLE
AND LOW-KEY, OKAY?

09:53.326 --> 09:54.094
- SIMPLE AND LOW-KEY IT IS.

09:54.127 --> 09:55.729
I THOUGHT WE COULD
GO TO DINNER.

09:55.763 --> 09:59.366
- SOMEPLACE EASY AND CASUAL,
NOTHING FANCY.

09:59.399 --> 10:01.769
- HOW ABOUT
THE LIBERTY DINER?

10:01.802 --> 10:02.736
- NOT THAT CASUAL.
[chuckles]

10:02.770 --> 10:04.772
- LOOK, HOW ABOUT I MEET YOU
AT YOUR PLACE?

10:04.805 --> 10:06.039
UM, WHAT TIME
DO YOU GET HOME?

10:06.073 --> 10:10.010
- AH, IF I HAD MY DAMN PALM, I
COULD TELL YOU FOR SURE, BUT...

10:10.043 --> 10:11.979
LET'S SEE, I'VE GOT CLASSES
TILL 4:00,

10:12.012 --> 10:14.381
THEN THE DOCTOR'S,
THEN YOGA, SO...

10:14.414 --> 10:17.651
I'D SAY AROUND 7:00.
UM, NO, YOU BETTER MAKE IT 7:30.

10:17.685 --> 10:18.786
- PERFECT.

10:18.819 --> 10:20.320
- BEN.

10:20.353 --> 10:22.923
- HEY, PAUL.
[grunts]

10:22.956 --> 10:24.124
- HOW ARE YOU DOING, BABY?

10:24.157 --> 10:25.258
- MM, GOOD.
GOOD. YOU?

10:25.292 --> 10:26.860
- AH, NO COMPLAINTS.

10:26.894 --> 10:27.928
- PAUL, THIS IS MICHAEL.

10:27.961 --> 10:30.130
- OH, MICHAEL.

10:30.163 --> 10:31.732
I HEARD YOU WERE SEEING
SOMEONE.

10:31.765 --> 10:33.133
- WORD TRAVELS FAST.

10:33.166 --> 10:35.135
- [laughs]
AROUND HERE?

10:35.168 --> 10:37.304
UH, LISTEN, UH,
WE SHOULD GET TOGETHER.

10:37.337 --> 10:38.706
WHY DON'T YOU CALL ME
SOMETIME?

10:38.739 --> 10:41.008
- I WILL, I'LL DO THAT.
- GOOD.

10:41.041 --> 10:43.110
SEE YOU, MICHAEL.
both: SEE YOU.

10:43.143 --> 10:45.378
- NICE GUY.
- PAUL? OH, YEAH, HE'S...

10:45.412 --> 10:46.513
HE'S A SWEETHEART.

10:46.546 --> 10:50.017
ACTUALLY, HE AND I WERE
TOGETHER ABOUT FIVE YEARS AGO.

10:50.050 --> 10:51.151
- OH.

10:51.184 --> 10:53.887
- NO, WE STAYED FRIENDS,
AL--

10:53.921 --> 10:56.323
ALTHOUGH AT THE TIME,
IT WAS NOT EASY.

10:56.356 --> 10:57.825
- WAIT, ISN'T THAT
ABOUT THE TIME

10:57.858 --> 10:58.859
THAT YOU FOUND OUT
THAT YOU WERE...

10:58.892 --> 10:59.860
- POSITIVE, YEAH.

10:59.893 --> 11:01.061
HE'S THE ONE
WHO INFECTED ME.

11:01.094 --> 11:02.796
- HOLY FUCK.

11:02.830 --> 11:04.732
- NO, NO, NO, IT'S...

11:04.765 --> 11:06.166
IT'S OKAY.

11:06.199 --> 11:09.436
HE DIDN'T KNOW AND I-I
SHOULD'VE BEEN MORE CAREFUL.

11:09.469 --> 11:11.939
ANYWAY, I'VE, UH...

11:11.972 --> 11:13.907
I'VE FORGIVEN HIM.

11:19.346 --> 11:20.781
- THE MAN IS PERFECT.

11:20.814 --> 11:21.915
THERE'S NO OTHER EXPLANATION.

11:21.949 --> 11:24.251
HOW ELSE COULD YOU FORGIVE
THE GUY WHO INFECTED YOU?

11:24.284 --> 11:26.119
- [snorts]
TRY NUTS.

11:26.153 --> 11:28.321
- IF IT WERE ME,
I'D WANT TO KILL HIM.

11:28.355 --> 11:29.990
- BEN'S NOT LIKE THAT.

11:30.023 --> 11:32.292
HE'S MANAGED TO FREE HIMSELF
FROM ALL THE EMOTIONAL BAGGAGE

11:32.325 --> 11:33.861
THAT THE REST OF US
CARRY AROUND.

11:33.894 --> 11:34.828
- I WONDER HOW HE DOES IT.

11:34.862 --> 11:37.330
- MY GUESS,
HE SINGS A LOT OF SHOW TUNES.

11:37.364 --> 11:38.899
- YOU WEREN'T DOING
SUCH A BAD JOB,

11:38.932 --> 11:41.134
BELTING THEM OUT.
- WHAT ABOUT YOU?

11:41.168 --> 11:43.203
YOUR DUET
WITH THE BOY INGENUE?

11:43.236 --> 11:45.072
- AH, YOU MEAN SAINT LUKE?

11:45.105 --> 11:46.940
- SOMETHING TELLS ME
YOUR INTEREST IN HIM

11:46.974 --> 11:48.375
ISN'T ENTIRELY SPIRITUAL.

11:48.408 --> 11:51.111
- HE IS THE SWEETEST,
THE KINDEST, THE...

11:51.144 --> 11:53.380
SEXIEST, MOST ADORABLE GUY
I'VE EVER MET.

11:53.413 --> 11:54.948
- SO WHAT DOES HE THINK
ABOUT YOU?

11:54.982 --> 11:57.050
- HE THINKS I RUN
A RELIEF ORGANIZATION.

11:57.084 --> 11:58.318
- WHAT?
- WHAT?

11:58.351 --> 11:59.319
- WHAT?
- WHAT?

11:59.352 --> 12:00.353
- WHAT?
- WHAT?

12:00.387 --> 12:01.889
- YEP.

12:01.922 --> 12:04.091
ME, THE RED CROSS,
AND THE UNICEF.

12:04.124 --> 12:06.994
- AND HOW, PRAY, DID HE GET
THAT IMPRESSION?

12:07.027 --> 12:10.230
- WELL, HE ASKED ME
WHAT I DID, AND I, UH--

12:10.263 --> 12:12.199
- LIED?

12:13.466 --> 12:14.935
- WHY THE HELL DID YOU
DO THAT?

12:14.968 --> 12:16.970
- HE'S A CHURCH-GOING
ELEMENTARY SCHOOL TEACHER

12:17.004 --> 12:18.505
WHO DOES CHARITY WORK,
FOR FUCK'S SAKE.

12:18.538 --> 12:20.373
I MEAN, WHAT WOULD HE THINK
IF I TOLD HIM I'M THE CEO

12:20.407 --> 12:22.309
OF JERKATWORK.NET?

12:22.342 --> 12:24.144
- WELL, IF HE'S AS PERFECT
AS YOU SAY,

12:24.177 --> 12:26.346
HE PROBABLY WOULDN'T CARE.

12:26.379 --> 12:28.548
- [groans]
WELL, BOYS...

12:28.581 --> 12:30.083
YOU DATE YOUR SAINTS.

12:30.117 --> 12:32.152
I'LL STICK TO THE SINNERS.

12:35.355 --> 12:37.825
- BUT IT'S HIS BIRTHDAY,
FOR CHRIST'S SAKES.

12:37.858 --> 12:39.793
- COULDN'T YOU AT LEAST
HAVE A CAKE?

12:39.827 --> 12:42.129
- I DON'T NEED ANY CAKE.
I GAINED THREE OUNCES LAST WEEK.

12:42.162 --> 12:43.964
NOW, WILL YOU PLEASE
GET OFF MY BACK?

12:43.997 --> 12:46.166
I HAVE A SHITLOAD
OF WORK TO DO.

12:46.199 --> 12:48.135
- HEY, YOU LOOK SPIFFY.

12:48.168 --> 12:49.402
- A NEW SPORT COAT?

12:49.436 --> 12:52.072
- YEP. MY MOM GOT IT FOR ME
FOR MY BIRTHDAY.

12:52.105 --> 12:56.276
- DIDN'T YOUR DADDY EVER
TEACH YOU HOW TO TIE A TIE?

12:56.309 --> 12:57.878
- NO, HE WAS TOO BUSY
KICKING ME OUT

12:57.911 --> 12:59.512
AND BEATING THE SHIT
OUT OF YOU.

12:59.546 --> 13:01.281
- WELL, NEITHER DID MINE.

13:01.314 --> 13:03.516
HE WAS TOO BUSY
REGRETTING THE DAY I WAS BORN.

13:03.550 --> 13:04.517
COME HERE.

13:04.551 --> 13:06.486
- * ALL RIGHT

13:06.519 --> 13:08.889
* YOU'RE GETTING
WAY TOO CLOSE *

13:08.922 --> 13:10.924
* ALL RIGHT

13:10.958 --> 13:13.093
* SMELLIN' LIKE A ROSE

13:13.126 --> 13:14.895
* COME ON

13:14.928 --> 13:17.430
- THIS ISN'T THE BIRTHDAY SUIT
I'D LIKE TO SEE YOU IN.

13:17.464 --> 13:19.566
[chuckles]

13:19.599 --> 13:21.468
- * AND FIND A BETTER WAY

13:21.501 --> 13:22.836
- THERE, NOW.

13:22.870 --> 13:24.437
GO GET SOME CULTURE.

13:24.471 --> 13:27.240
*

13:27.274 --> 13:30.243
- DON'T WORK TOO HARD.

13:30.277 --> 13:35.949
*

13:35.983 --> 13:38.485
- I'LL CATCH UP WITH YOU.

13:38.518 --> 13:39.586
*

13:39.619 --> 13:42.222
- * WHAT HAVE WE GOT,
YOU AND ME *

13:42.255 --> 13:43.423
- DID YOU FORGET SOMETHING?

13:43.456 --> 13:45.325
- I DON'T UNDERSTAND YOU.

13:45.358 --> 13:46.894
- FEW DO.

13:46.927 --> 13:48.361
- IT'S OBVIOUS HOW MUCH
YOU LOVE HIM,

13:48.395 --> 13:50.197
YET YOU WON'T CELEBRATE
HIS BIRTHDAY

13:50.230 --> 13:52.232
BECAUSE YOU DON'T CONSIDER
IT AN ACCOMPLISHMENT.

13:52.265 --> 13:54.201
WELL, ISN'T IT AN
ACCOMPLISHMENT THAT HE'S ALIVE

13:54.234 --> 13:55.335
AND WELL?

13:55.368 --> 13:57.070
ISN'T THAT ENOUGH REASON
TO CELEBRATE?

13:57.104 --> 14:00.307
- * MAKE MY DAY
WHEN YOU MAKE MY NIGHT *

14:00.340 --> 14:04.945
* MAKE MY DAY
STEPPING INTO THE LIGHT *

14:04.978 --> 14:09.049
* MAKE MY DAY
WHEN YOU MAKE MY NIGHT *

14:09.082 --> 14:11.084
* ALL RIGHT
[door slams]

14:11.118 --> 14:13.186
* YOU'RE GETTING
WAY TOO CLOSE *

14:13.220 --> 14:16.189
[intense violin music]

14:16.223 --> 14:24.164
*

15:41.774 --> 15:43.643
- I FOUND IT.

15:43.676 --> 15:47.414
I WORE IT TO THE WHAT-A-DRAG
BALL IN '89.

15:47.447 --> 15:49.382
I WENT AS CHO-CHO-SAN.
- [laughs]

15:49.416 --> 15:51.651
- YOUR MOTHER WENT
AS PINKERTON.

15:51.684 --> 15:53.586
I PROMISED EMMETT HE COULD
BORROW IT FOR THE PARTY.

15:53.620 --> 15:56.156
- IT WILL MAKE
A FABULOUS HOSTESS GOWN.

15:56.189 --> 15:58.491
- HE'LL BE STUNNING.

15:58.525 --> 16:00.493
- JUST DON'T BE LATE.

16:00.527 --> 16:02.229
- AND DON'T YOU BE NERVOUS.

16:02.262 --> 16:03.730
- I JUST WANT EVERYTHING
TO COME OFF AS PLANNED,

16:03.763 --> 16:05.132
YOU KNOW, FOR BEN.

16:05.165 --> 16:07.734
- IT'LL BE THE SOCIAL EVENT
OF THE SEASON.

16:07.767 --> 16:09.336
- WHAT'S THE SOCIAL EVENT
OF THE SEASON?

16:09.369 --> 16:11.704
THE HOMO HOP AT BABYLON?

16:11.738 --> 16:14.474
- BEN'S SURPRISE PARTY.

16:14.507 --> 16:16.209
- OH.

16:16.243 --> 16:17.344
- [clears throat]

16:17.377 --> 16:19.712
I WAS JUST TELLING VIC
NOT TO BE LATE.

16:19.746 --> 16:22.749
- UH-HUH.

16:22.782 --> 16:24.617
- YOU KNOW...

16:24.651 --> 16:26.686
IF YOU WANT TO COME...

16:26.719 --> 16:29.222
- AH, THAT'S OKAY.
I GOT PLANS. I'M--

16:29.256 --> 16:33.226
I'M, UH, I-I'M GOING
TO THE MOVIES WITH MY--MY--

16:33.260 --> 16:35.595
MY FRIEND ROSIE.

16:35.628 --> 16:37.097
B-BUT PLEASE,

16:37.130 --> 16:39.399
WISH HIM MANY HAPPY RETURNS
FOR ME.

16:42.669 --> 16:45.672
- I WILL.

16:45.705 --> 16:47.307
AND I'LL BE SURE TO GIVE THIS
TO EMMETT.

16:47.340 --> 16:49.409
THANKS.
- SEE YOU, MICHAEL.

16:58.818 --> 17:02.755
YOU HAVEN'T SPOKEN TO ROSIE
IN...12 YEARS?

17:02.789 --> 17:04.457
- WELL, YOU NEVER KNOW,
SHE MAY CALL.

17:04.491 --> 17:06.226
HERE, HELP ME WITH THIS.

17:12.265 --> 17:14.201
- I THOUGHT YOU WERE GOING
TO MAKE MORE OF AN EFFORT

17:14.234 --> 17:15.768
WHERE MICHAEL AND BEN
ARE CONCERNED.

17:15.802 --> 17:17.637
- DO YOU SEE ME GIVING HIM
ANY GRIEF?

17:17.670 --> 17:20.240
- I DON'T SEE YOU GIVING HIM
ANY JOY.

17:20.273 --> 17:24.811
- I AGREED TO TOLERATE IT,
NOT ENDORSE IT.

17:24.844 --> 17:27.314
- WELL, MAYBE YOU COULD
UP YOUR COMMITMENT A NOTCH.

17:27.347 --> 17:28.748
YOU'VE GOT TO ADMIT,

17:28.781 --> 17:30.683
BEN'S BEEN
A POSITIVE INFLUENCE ON HIM.

17:30.717 --> 17:33.386
- POSITIVE?
EXACTLY.

17:33.420 --> 17:34.821
- AND DESPITE
ALL OF YOUR DARKEST FEARS

17:34.854 --> 17:36.289
AND DIRE PREDICTIONS,

17:36.323 --> 17:40.160
THEY BOTH SEEM TO BE
DOING JUST FINE.

17:40.193 --> 17:42.762
SO WHY NOT BE A SPORT...

17:42.795 --> 17:44.731
AND MAKE THE KID HAPPY?

17:49.502 --> 17:51.471
- WAS HE AMAZING OR WHAT?

17:51.504 --> 17:54.207
- AND TO THINK
THAT HE'S SO YOUNG.

17:54.241 --> 17:56.409
- HE STARTED PLAYING
WHEN HE WAS FOUR.

17:56.443 --> 17:58.445
HE STUDIED WITH THE GREAT
ANDREI VISHNEVSKI.

17:58.478 --> 18:00.380
- I THOUGHT YOU DIDN'T KNOW
ANYTHING ABOUT CLASSICAL MUSIC.

18:00.413 --> 18:02.182
- I READ THE PROGRAM.

18:02.215 --> 18:04.717
- I THINK WE'RE WITNESSING
A CONVERSION EXPERIENCE.

18:04.751 --> 18:07.554
- ANOTHER LESBIAN
SUCCESS STORY. HMM.

18:07.587 --> 18:09.456
- YES.

18:09.489 --> 18:11.591
OH, THERE'S SUSAN. I'D BETTER
THANK HER FOR THE TICKETS.

18:11.624 --> 18:12.625
OH, EXCUSE ME.

18:12.659 --> 18:16.729
[indistinct chatter]

18:18.698 --> 18:20.300
- THANK YOU FOR COMING.

18:26.673 --> 18:29.276
- I JUST WANTED TO SAY
I THOUGHT YOU WERE GREAT.

18:29.309 --> 18:33.246
- THE RAVEL WAS PASSABLE,
BUT THE BRAHMS WAS FOR SHIT.

18:33.280 --> 18:34.614
- I DIDN'T NOTICE.

18:34.647 --> 18:37.417
- YEAH, WELL, YOU SHOULD'VE.
IT WAS ALL YOUR FAULT.

18:37.450 --> 18:39.619
- ME?
- YES.

18:39.652 --> 18:43.656
THE WAY YOU WERE STARING
AT ME WAS VERY DISTRACTING.

18:43.690 --> 18:45.392
- I'M SORRY.

18:45.425 --> 18:48.461
- ALTHOUGH NOT NECESSARILY
IN A BAD WAY.

18:48.495 --> 18:50.597
- HEH.
YEAH, I'M JUSTIN.

18:50.630 --> 18:53.366
- ETHAN.
- I KNOW.

18:53.400 --> 18:54.901
- WHAT'S THIS?

18:54.934 --> 18:57.670
- OH, IT'S NOTHING.
- LET ME SEE.

19:04.411 --> 19:07.414
IT'S ME IN FIVE VARIATIONS.
- [chuckles]

19:07.447 --> 19:09.782
IT'S A HABIT.
YOU KNOW, I CAN'T...

19:09.816 --> 19:11.384
STOP MYSELF.
[chuckles]

19:11.418 --> 19:13.186
- IT'S THE SIGN
OF A TRUE ARTIST.

19:13.220 --> 19:15.555
I PLAY IN MY SLEEP.

19:15.588 --> 19:16.756
YOU GO TO SCHOOL HERE,
RIGHT?

19:16.789 --> 19:18.625
- VISUAL ARTS.
- YEAH.

19:18.658 --> 19:20.560
YEAH, I THOUGHT
I RECOGNIZED YOU.

19:20.593 --> 19:23.196
- SOME FRIENDS BROUGHT ME
FOR MY BIRTHDAY.

19:24.764 --> 19:27.166
- [singsong]
HELLO.

19:29.402 --> 19:31.604
- HERE.
HAPPY BIRTHDAY.

19:31.638 --> 19:33.673
- IT'S YOUR OWN CD.
- YEAH, I MADE IT MYSELF.

19:33.706 --> 19:35.442
A COUPLE OF MOZART
SONATAS, A...

19:35.475 --> 19:37.677
DEBUSSY,
A LITTLE BERNSTEIN.

19:37.710 --> 19:39.812
- HEH.
NICE PHOTO.

19:39.846 --> 19:43.316
- YEAH, WELL, NEXT TIME,
I'M GOING TO USE ONE OF THESE.

19:43.350 --> 19:45.518
- DO.
- ETHAN.

19:45.552 --> 19:47.554
GOOD JOB.
- HI, HOW'RE YOU DOING?

19:47.587 --> 19:48.788
GOOD TO SEE YOU.

19:48.821 --> 19:50.490
I HAVEN'T SEEN YOU GUYS
IN SO LONG.

19:50.523 --> 19:54.527
- WELL, IT'S BEEN, UH,
WHAT, TWO OR THREE MONTHS?

19:59.599 --> 20:01.200
- [breathing heavily]

20:05.805 --> 20:08.741
[sighs deeply]

20:13.313 --> 20:14.447
OHH.

20:14.481 --> 20:16.583
- MMM.

20:17.950 --> 20:19.986
- OHH.

20:28.895 --> 20:30.663
- YOU...

20:30.697 --> 20:34.301
ARE A WONDERFUL LOVER, TED.

20:34.334 --> 20:38.338
YOU'RE SO NICE,
SO SINCERE...

20:38.371 --> 20:41.941
SO HONEST.

20:41.974 --> 20:44.444
I FELT IMMEDIATELY

20:44.477 --> 20:47.013
THAT YOU'RE SOMEONE
I COULD TRUST.

20:47.046 --> 20:48.581
- [chuckles]

20:48.615 --> 20:50.417
[stammering]

20:50.450 --> 20:52.719
YOU REMEMBER, UH,
WHEN YOU ASKED ME WHAT I DID,

20:52.752 --> 20:55.021
AND THEN--
AND I SAID I...

20:55.054 --> 20:56.889
I WORKED IN COMPUTERS?

20:56.923 --> 20:59.292
- MM-HMM, AND THAT YOU'RE
A SERVICE PROVIDER

20:59.326 --> 21:02.729
FOR A RELIEF ORGANIZATION.

21:02.762 --> 21:05.632
- [chuckles]
YEAH, UM...

21:05.665 --> 21:07.867
W-WELL, THAT'S--THAT'S NOT
COMPLETELY ACCURATE,

21:07.900 --> 21:11.938
ALTHOUGH...
I CAN UNDERSTAND FROM...

21:11.971 --> 21:14.874
HOW INTENTIONALLY AMBIGUOUS
I WAS ABOUT MY JOB DESCRIPTION

21:14.907 --> 21:19.512
THAT YOU...
MIGHT ASSUME THAT, UH...

21:19.546 --> 21:21.348
THAT I SHIP
FOOD AND CLOTHING

21:21.381 --> 21:25.017
TO WAR-TORN REGIONS
OF THE GLOBE, WHEN...

21:25.051 --> 21:27.354
IN FACT, UH...

21:27.387 --> 21:29.689
THE SERVICE I PROVIDE...

21:31.958 --> 21:34.527
[clears throat]

21:34.561 --> 21:36.396
IT'S A PORN SITE.

21:36.429 --> 21:41.468
AND, UH, THE RELIEF
COMES FROM...

21:43.436 --> 21:46.606
WELL, I'M SURE YOU
CAN FIGURE OUT THE REST.

21:46.639 --> 21:49.809
[clock ticking]

21:49.842 --> 21:51.911
[both sigh]

21:51.944 --> 21:53.980
WELL, I GUESS
WE'D BETTER GET DRESSED.

21:54.013 --> 21:56.383
- NO, WAIT.

22:00.853 --> 22:04.891
IS THAT WHAT YOU
WANTED TO TELL ME?

22:04.924 --> 22:06.526
- WELL, YEAH, I-I,
YOU KNOW, I THOUGHT,

22:06.559 --> 22:08.795
AFTER EVERYTHING YOU TOLD ME
ABOUT YOURSELF THAT...

22:08.828 --> 22:12.699
YOU KNOW, YOU MIGHT...

22:12.732 --> 22:16.135
- NO, NO.

22:16.168 --> 22:19.639
I'VE EVEN
BEEN ON THEM MYSELF.

22:19.672 --> 22:22.675
COUPLE TIMES.

22:22.709 --> 22:26.579
- YOU HAVE?
- MM-HMM.

22:26.613 --> 22:30.149
- AND YOU DON'T MIND?

22:30.182 --> 22:33.586
- NO. NO.

22:33.620 --> 22:37.590
LOOK.

22:37.624 --> 22:42.028
YOU'RE WHAT MATTERS.

22:42.061 --> 22:44.897
- [sighs]

22:51.971 --> 22:54.874
- IT WAS INCREDIBLE.
[violin playing on CD]

22:54.907 --> 22:57.143
- HOOKED ON CLASSICS,
ARE WE?

22:57.176 --> 22:58.811
- YEAH, AND THE GUY
THAT PLAYED THE VIOLIN,

22:58.845 --> 23:01.047
I WISH YOU COULD'VE
BEEN THERE, HE WAS...

23:01.080 --> 23:05.618
HE WAS INCREDIBLE.
- INCREDIBLE, EH?

23:05.652 --> 23:07.954
- YOU KNOW,
IT WOULDN'T HURT YOU

23:07.987 --> 23:11.458
TO EXPOSE YOURSELF
TO SOME CULTURE.

23:11.491 --> 23:13.993
- I'VE EXPOSED MYSELF
TO A LITTLE CULTURE.

23:14.026 --> 23:16.763
THERE WAS AN OBOE PLAYER
I MET AT THE BATHS ONCE.

23:16.796 --> 23:17.864
- OHH.

23:17.897 --> 23:25.838
*

23:32.812 --> 23:37.784
- ARE YOU UP FOR ANOTHER
BIRTHDAY TREAT?

23:37.817 --> 23:40.653
- NO WAY.

23:40.687 --> 23:42.789
[chuckles]

23:42.822 --> 23:46.058
NO FUCKING WAY.

23:46.092 --> 23:47.794
I KNEW IT.

23:47.827 --> 23:49.796
ALL THAT BULLSHIT
ABOUT NOT DOING BIRTHDAYS.

23:49.829 --> 23:52.799
YOU WERE JUST GOING
TO SURPRISE ME.

23:52.832 --> 23:55.034
OHH.

23:55.067 --> 23:59.506
WHAT IS IT?

23:59.539 --> 24:01.708
- THIS WAY, YOUNG MAN.

24:03.576 --> 24:05.211
- I'M GOING TO TRIP.

24:05.244 --> 24:06.946
[yelps]

24:15.888 --> 24:18.190
- [imitates motor buzzing]

24:18.224 --> 24:21.828
- HAPPY BIRTHDAY.

24:21.861 --> 24:24.664
- HAPPY BIRTHDAY.

24:24.697 --> 24:27.800
DO YOU LIKE YOUR PRESENT?

24:27.834 --> 24:30.202
HE LOOKS JUST LIKE
THAT UNDERWEAR MODEL

24:30.236 --> 24:32.539
YOU LIKE, DOESN'T HE?

24:32.572 --> 24:36.743
ARE YOU GOING TO UNWRAP IT?

25:08.808 --> 25:10.677
- HI.
[gong crashes]

25:10.710 --> 25:12.612
- [bad Asian accent]
WELCOME, KIND GENTLEMEN.

25:12.645 --> 25:13.913
PLEASE ENTER.

25:13.946 --> 25:16.583
I AM YOUR HOSTESS
FOR THE EVENING.

25:16.616 --> 25:18.150
[shy giggle]

25:18.184 --> 25:20.086
- EMMETT, IS THAT YOU?

25:20.119 --> 25:24.624
- YEAH, HONEY.
WHAT DO YOU THINK?

25:24.657 --> 25:26.292
- YOU PUT THE "GAY"
BACK IN GEISHA.

25:26.325 --> 25:27.093
- AWW.

25:27.126 --> 25:28.628
- COME ON, HURRY UP
AND GET IN.

25:28.661 --> 25:30.129
HE'S GOING TO BE HERE
ANY MINUTE.

25:30.162 --> 25:31.330
[Emmett gasping]

25:31.363 --> 25:33.299
[soft Japanese music]

25:33.332 --> 25:35.267
- UH, MICHAEL,

25:35.301 --> 25:37.637
M. BUTTERFLY...

25:37.670 --> 25:39.572
THIS IS LUKE.
- UH, LUKE, RIGHT.

25:39.606 --> 25:41.874
WE, UH, WE MET AT THE CHURCH
OF THE HOLY SHOW TUNE.

25:41.908 --> 25:43.175
- RIGHT.

25:43.209 --> 25:44.911
IT'S NICE TO MEET YOU, LUKE.

25:44.944 --> 25:46.178
- JESUS.

25:46.212 --> 25:47.313
